               <head>Hariri's Maqamat, translation and commentary</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharḥ-i Maqāmāt-i Ḥarīrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100064 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85113635 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85077509 https://lccn.loc.gov/gf2014026425 https://lccn.loc.gov/gf2014026479" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_453Cx-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21758">Sharḥ-i Maqāmāt-i Ḥarīrī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21758">شرح مقامات حريري</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Translation and commentary (mamzūj) on Ḥarīrī's Maqāmāt </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning, commencing with the fifteenth maqāmah </p>
                        <p>The author's name does not appear </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon fragmentary (f. 452v): dated regnal year 40 [of <persName key="person_6178410" role="oth">Emperor ʿĀlamgīr</persName>] (circa 1698) by <persName key="person_f7619" role="scr">Sulṭān Muḥammad Siyālk[ūtī] </persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Neat scribal naskh throughout; Arabic quotations in red </p>
                        <p>Annotated in margins </p>
                        <p>Unbound; boards missing; severly damaged by tears at end and wormholes; fragile </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
